         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">15/5/93. ¶  ¶ By this mail, dear Dr Dyer, I send a fungus, which during the last 46 years of my Australian observations I have never yet seen, so far as I remember. I hope, Dr Cooke ¶  will grant the ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">93.05.15</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew Correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1891-1896, f. 46.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Annotated</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">in</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">black ink by John Baker</seg>:<seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>Seen by Massee | JGB 22/6/93 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">and in pencil by Thiselton-Dyer</seg>:<seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>And 22/6/<seg style="font-style: italic; ">93 [letter not found].</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>15/5/93.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>By this mail, dear Dr Dyer, I send a fungus, which during the last 46 years of my Australian observations I have never yet seen, so far as I remember. I hope, Dr Cooke<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">John Baker wrote </seg>retired <seg style="font-style: italic; ">in black ink in the margin next to </seg>Dr Cooke, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">which is underlined in the same ink.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> will grant the little reward to the discoverer, Mr Reader,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Probably Felix Reader.</p>
               </note> to have his name attached to it, if this fungus should prove new. But now a days, when 30000 sp are described for Mycology not to speak of many more synonyms, it is only wasting time of those who cannot give up all their time to mycology, attempting to name fungs except the more common kinds. </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The fructifying summit with its sporidia reminds of the theca of [a Sphagnum]<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Obscured by binding strip.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The discovery of <name key="Fagus%20Moorei%20">Fagus Moorei </name>by an <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Amateur</hi>
               </seg> not far from Moreton Bay within <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Queensland territory</hi>
               </seg> proves, how imperfectly the large and now easily traversable area there is explored for plants. The Gov Botanist of QL. should first elaborate a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">full</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Flora</hi>
               </seg> of his own extensive province, and make himself <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">personally</hi>
               </seg> acquainted with each of its districts, before attempting to write a supplement to Bentham's 7 volumes, for which I have vast materials since 1864, while he has no personal experiences outside of QL. anywhere in Australia, nor material (and little authenticated)<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">and little authenticated <seg style="font-style: italic; ">is written in the left margin on the back of the MS folio, its position in the text indicated by asterisks. Parentheses added editorially for clarity.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> of any appreciable extent from the other colonies, so that he would have to take out of my Fragmenta and other works of mine the additions and that without permission of his preceptor who led him to Austral Botany<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See Clements (1998) for the reaction by M to F. Bailey's proposal to write a supplement to Bentham's <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Flora australiensis</seg>. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No similar trespass is known as attempted in our Science, before.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">No similar trespass ... before <seg style="font-style: italic; ">is written in the central margin on the front of the folio. </seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall accept for convenience sake for my suppl. the sequence of Benth[s] flora for my supplement.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">I shall accept ... for my supplement <seg style="font-style: italic; ">is written in the central margin on the back of the folio</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #0000ff; ">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> altho not even in B &amp; H genera<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862–83).</p>
               </note> always adhered to.<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">altho not even in B &amp; H genera always adhered to <seg style="font-style: italic; ">is written in the right margin on the back of the folio.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Why does <name key="Cordyceps%20Taylori%20">Cordyceps Taylori </name>not occur in Dr Cooke's [Austr] Fungus-Flora?<note xml:id="ftn11" type="footnote" n="11">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Cooke (1892). </p>
               </note> Though even on the cover of his "plant-worms"<note xml:id="ftn12" type="footnote" n="12">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The figure of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Cordyceps taylori</seg> on p. 159 of Cooke (1892b) is also used on the embossed cover.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cordyceps%20Taylori%20">Cordyceps Taylori </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Fagus%20Moorei%20">Fagus Moorei </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Sphagnum%20">Sphagnum </name>
            </p>
         </div>
